    {
        "content": "<p>Hello, I'm wondering if anyone has tips for making statements about functions in relation to different types of asymptotes:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/8E5nl6_45p3VRqdMcHf58Uuy/image.png\">image.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/8E5nl6_45p3VRqdMcHf58Uuy/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/8E5nl6_45p3VRqdMcHf58Uuy/image.png\"></a></div><p>After some searching in mathlib I found : <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs_demo/analysis/asymptotics/asymptotic_equivalent.html\">https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs_demo/analysis/asymptotics/asymptotic_equivalent.html</a> . But It's not talking about what I'm looking for. </p>\n<p>I think I know how to do horizontal asymptotes (just use a limit as x tends to +- infinity), but I'm not really sure how to deal with the vertical ones. If someone could give a MWE that displays a statement about each of the  types of asymptotes (like the ones I've included in the image) I would be very grateful!</p>",
        "id": 273171433,
        "sender_full_name": "Callum Cassidy-Nolan",
        "timestamp": 1645750506
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here are examples of each </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">topology.instances.real</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span> <span class=\"n\">filter</span>\n<span class=\"n\">open_locale</span> <span class=\"n\">topological_space</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ 0âº of xâ»Â¹ is âˆ</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">tendsto</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">â»Â¹</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">at_top</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ 0â» of xâ»Â¹ is -âˆ</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">tendsto</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">â»Â¹</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">at_bot</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ âˆ of xâ»Â¹ is 0</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">tendsto</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">â»Â¹</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">at_top</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- limit as x â†’ -âˆ of xâ»Â¹ is 0</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">tendsto</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">â»Â¹</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">at_bot</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ“</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
